HEADWORD: Pantoscopic
<hw>Pan`to*scop"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Panto-</ets> + <ets>-scope</ets> + <ets>-ic</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Literally, seeing everything; -- a term applied to eyeglasses or
spectacles divided into two segments, the upper being designed for
distant vision, the lower for vision of near objects.</def><-- = bifocal
-->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pantry</ent>⟦br⟧
